dublin_core.dcvalue: Wide field handheld high frequency ultrasonography using a variable high frequency ultrasound system is an imaging modality in the frequency range of 35 to 50 MHz Using a water bath immersion technique high resolution digital movies obtained from a variety of anterior segment ocular conditions were particularly helpful in establishing the diagnosis in each case Images taken with the wide field limbus to limbus mode provided a comprehensive picture of large and extensive lesions whereas the focal mode was for small to medium lesions or specific areas of interest
